Outside of test src sets, you can code your own await. Take a look at geode-core/src/main/java/org/apache/geode/distributed/internal/locks/DLockService.java's sleep method.

Maybe change it to just throw InterruptedException and add a condition (for example, if want to wait until the pidFile disappears from the JVM's working directory):
```
  private void awaitPidFileDeletion(long millis) throws InterruptedException {
    StopWatch timer = new StopWatch(true);
    while (pidFile.exists()) {
      long timeLeft = millis - timer.elapsedTimeMillis();
      if (timeLeft <= 0) {
        break;
      }
      Thread.sleep(timeLeft);
      break;
    }
  }
```

